	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p>To the Reader</p>
				<p>The events of the life of this Great Man have arising separately<lb/> with the events in the chains of wisdom and learning which<lb/> have gone forth &#38; been exchanged &#40;spread abroad&#41; in the march of<lb/> the last seventy years.  For all his works &#38; deeds in which<lb/> he laboured &#38; toiled all the days of his &#40;fleeting&#41; life&#44; there are<lb/> weaved in &#38; intertwined in the midst of these new intelli&#61;<lb/>gencies.  And who is the man who has watched over &#40;gives<lb/> attention&#41; &#91;the opening of&#93; the gates of wisdom to see the wonders &#38; doings which<lb/> these latter days have brought forth upon us &#38; whose lips<lb/> have not chaunted <del>the</del> <sic>praize</sic> whilst reaching out this great<lb/> one.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Wherefore I have brought forth from my heart &#40;<hi rend="underline">al</hi>&#45;<lb/><hi rend="underline">ready</hi> prepared <hi rend="underline">for it</hi>&#41; to narrate also to the sons of our<lb/> people who long to hear words in the Hebrew Tongue&#44; the<lb/> genealogy of this beloved person&#44; so that they may<lb/> warm up their hearts over the glory honor of the many &#40;kinds<lb/> of&#41; knowledge which have been spread over the Earth<lb/> in these our days&#59; and to see in them the labors and<lb/> mighty <add>Hebrew</add> which have wearied&#44; but not exhausted by<lb/> them their researches all their fleeting days to disclose the<lb/> hidden places of wisdom&#44; and to bring forth the truth for its own<lb/> sake.  And also&#44; in order to raise up establish in this way a memo&#45;<lb/>rial to this wise name in the <add>&#63;</add> of the Hebrew Language</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>an additional <hi rend="underline">binding</hi> <del>which will adorn</del> his great wisdom&#44; <add>Hebrew</add> his justice<lb/> and righteousness to the happiness <add>&#63;</add> the children of <placeName>Israel</placeName>.<lb/>  Speaking well of them before all peoples &#38; tongues.  And<lb/> every Israelite who loves his people will rejoice in his<lb/> heart&#44; will fill his mouth with praise &#38; thanksgiving to the<lb/> honor of this beloved wise man&#44; whose name shall<lb/> flourish as long as the sun remains and his righteousness<lb/> will stand forever.</p>
				<p><placeName>Berlin</placeName> <date>September 1857</date>.</p>
				<p><add>&#63;</add> <add>Hebrew</add></p>
		</body>
